{
  "_comment_purpose": "Single source of truth for critical-table classification used by openregs build + delta guards. validate_critical_tables (in scripts/05_build_database.py) uses the `floor` field; weekly_update.sh's snapshot_counts uses the `snapshot` field; weekly_update.sh's validate_delta uses the `growth` field. Adding a new critical table? Add it once here, not in three places.",
  "_comment_fields": {
    "floor": "Minimum row count below which the build aborts before deploy (validate_critical_tables raises SystemExit(5)). null = no absolute floor; tracked in delta/snapshot only.",
    "growth": "'incremental' = monotonically grows over time; any drop > 0.1% beyond noise is fatal in the delta guard. 'rebuild' = wiped+repopulated each run (e.g., full eCFR pull, staging-DB import); 5% drop tolerated in delta guard.",
    "snapshot": "true = include in pre/post-build snapshot for delta reporting + delta guard. Tables outside snapshot still get floor coverage if floor is non-null.",
    "smoke": "true = include in post-deploy smoke test (prod row count vs local) in deploy.sh. Keep this small (~5 tables) since each = one HTTPS round-trip to prod. Mirror of 990project/criticality.json field.",
    "db": "Which Datasette database the table lives in. Defaults to 'openregs' if omitted. Set to 'lobbying' for tables in lobbying.db. Only consulted by the post-deploy smoke test to route the curl URL + local file path."
  },
